#!/usr/bin/env bash
# SessionStart — remind the agent of the code-discovery protocol (profile-aware).
cat << 'REMINDER'
CRITICAL — Code Discovery Protocol:
1. Use your project's code-discovery MCP FIRST for ANY code exploration:
   - codebase-memory-mcp (cbm) for Python/TS/Go/... — search_graph / trace_path /
     get_code_snippet / query_graph / search_code / get_architecture
   - C# → serena(csharp) or a Roslyn MCP (e.g. CWM.RoslynNavigator): find_symbol /
     find_references / get_diagnostics
   - serena is the universal symbol-level fallback (find_symbol / search_for_pattern)
2. Use Grep/Glob/Read freely for text, configs, non-code files; always Read a file
   before editing it.
3. If the code graph is not indexed yet, index it FIRST (cbm index_repository, or let
   the Roslyn / serena language server load the solution).
REMINDER
